+[[ACE-memory]]
+=== `Zlm`: ACE Dedicated Memory Instructions
+
+The `Zlm` ACE extension requires the `Zlv` extension to be implemented, and
+adds two dedicated memory instructions: `ace.load` and `ace.store`. `Zlm` is
+mutually exclusive with `Zlio` and `Zlmv`.
+
+[[ACE-instruction-load]]
+==== `ace.load`
+
+_Encoding_::
+`ace.load` is an I-type instruction.
 +
+[wavedrom, , svg]
+....
+{reg:[
+    { bits:  7, name: 0x0b, attr: ['custom-0'] },
+    { bits:  5, name: 'context', attr: ['Kd','K{Xd}'] },
+    { bits:  3, name: 'ace.load', attr: ['0    0    0','0    0    1'] },
+    { bits:  5, name: 'Xs1' },
+    { bits: 12, name: 'immed12' },
+]}
+....
+
+_Mnemonics_::
+`ace.load{fournbsp}{nbsp}{nbsp}{nbsp}Kd|K{Xd}, %offset(Xs1)` +
+`ace.sysimport{nbsp}Kd|K{Xd}, %offset(Xs1)`
+
+_Description_::
++
+--
+`ace.load` imports a PI or a SCC into the CR `Kd` or `K{Xd}`, starting with the 8th byte of the MDH.
+The memory address of the latter is given in `%offset(Xs1)`.
+
+This instruction requires that the CR is ready to import information and that the first 8 bytes of the MDH have already been loaded by passing them as a parameter in a GPR (pair for RV32) to the `ace.setst` instruction used to open the CR for provisioning or import.
+
+If the _ConfigStatus_ field equals _CfgStComplete_, an invalid instruction exception is raised.
+
+`ace.load` can load data larger than the effective XLEN.
+`acestart` tracks the number of loaded bytes. If `ace.load` is interrupted,
+`acestart` contains the offset to the next byte to load upon resumption.
+
+// NOTE: Modifying the CR being used by an interrupted `ace.load` always forces
+// the load to restart. Software that aims to optimize this case must
+// inspect `ConfigStatus` in each CR's metadata to detect an incomplete load
+// and prevent the restart.
+
+The implementation first determines the size of the input to be loaded from the first 8 bytes of the MDH.
+The _ConfigStatus_ field determines the input type (PI or SCC), and
+the fields _Algorithm_, _AlgorithmPolicy_, and _KeyType_ determine its length.
+`ace.load` then requests the LSU to read the memory contents starting at `%offset(Xs1)`, in XLEN-bit sized loads,
+and copies them into the CR starting with the 8th byte (i.e., bits [127:64] of the MDH).
+The order in which the LSU issues these transactions is implementation dependent.
+See <<ACE-resumability-management>>, <<ACE-resumability-memory-model>> and <<ACE-export-import-algorithms>> for further details.
+
+When the key is in a system-defined format, the semantics of `ace.load`
+are entirely implementation dependent and do not assume that the CR has been readied to import information or
+that some metadata has already been loaded. System-defined format is signaled by the _SystemFormat_ bit of MDH[63:0], which in this case may have a system-defined length.
+
+The instruction may possibly modify state.
+
+The instruction is not usage-controlled.
 --
