+[[ACE-instruction-store]]
+===== `ace.store`
+
+_Encoding_::
+`ace.store` is an S-type instruction.
++
+[wavedrom, , svg]
+....
+{reg:[
+    { bits:  7, name: 0x27, attr: ['custom-1'] },
+    { bits:  5, name: 'immed[4:0]' },
+    { bits:  3, name: 'ace.store', attr: [0x0,0x1] },
+    { bits:  5, name: 'Xs1' },
+    { bits:  5, name: 'context', attr: ['Ks2','K{Xs2}'] },
+    { bits:  7, name: 'immed[11:5]' },
+]}
+....
+
+_Mnemonic_::
+`ace.store %offset(Xs1), Ks2|K{Xs2}`
+(((ACE, instruction, ace.export)))
+
+_Description_::
++
+--
+Exports raw data from the CR `Ks2` or `K{Xs2}`, starting with the 8th byte of the MDH, to memory at address `%offset(Xs1)`.
+
+The first 8 bytes of the MDH must be read from the CR using `ace.getmdl` and saved to memory by the software.
+
+`ace.store` can store data that may be larger than the effective XLEN.
+`acestart` keeps track of the number of stored bytes. If `ace.store` is
+interrupted, `acestart` contains the offset to the next byte to store upon
+resumption.
+
+NOTE: Modifying the CR being used by the interrupted `ace.store` always forces
+the store to restart. Software that aims to optimize this case will have to
+inspect `ConfigStatus` in the the metadata of each CR and detect if the store
+hasn't completed to impede the restart.
+
+If the _ConfigStatus_ field is equal to _CfgStComplete_, then an invalid instruction exception is raised.
+
+If the _ConfigStatus_ field is not equal to _CfgStComplete_
+the implementation first determines the size of the output to be generated from first 8 bytes of the MDH.
+The type of the output, i.e. whether it is a PI or a SCC, is determined by the _ConfigStatus_ field, and
+its length by _Algorithm_, _AlgorithmPolicy_, and _KeyType_.
+Then, `ace.store` requests the LSU to store the CR to memory, beginning with the 8th byte (i.e. bits [127:64] of the MDH),
+in XLEN-bit sized stores, in the memory region starting at address `%offset(Xs1)`.
+The order in which the LSU issues these transactions is implementation dependent.
+See <<ACE-resumability-management>>, <<ACE-resumability-memory-model>> and <<ACE-export-import-algorithms>> for further details.
+
+NOTE: We allow to store a PI because it may be possible that a provisioning operation be interrupted, and this allows
+resuming.
+
+The instruction does not modify state.
+
+The instruction is not usage-controlled.
